snippet.title: RESIDENT EVIL 9 REQUIEM Gameplay Trailer | Gamescom 2025
snippet.description:
Resident Evil 9 Requiem Gameplay Trailer revealed at Gamescom 2025. Capcom brings the next chapter of survival horror with RE9 Requiem, full trailer, gameplay and story details.

The wait is finally over! At Gamescom 2025, Capcom officially revealed the Resident Evil 9: Requiem Gameplay Trailer, and it’s everything survival horror fans have been hoping for. With jaw-dropping visuals, terrifying new enemies, and a chilling atmosphere, RE9 Requiem promises to take the legendary Resident Evil saga into a darker and more intense direction.

In this trailer, we get our first real look at Resident Evil 9 gameplay, showcasing the environments, combat mechanics, and cinematic storytelling that have defined the series for decades. The horror is back in full force, and every scene in this trailer hints at a new chapter that will connect past Resident Evil stories while introducing shocking new mysteries.

Fans are already speculating about the plot, characters, and locations featured in this trailer. Could RE9 Requiem be the scariest entry in the franchise yet? With Capcom pushing the boundaries of next-gen consoles, this could be one of the biggest survival horror releases of the decade.

On this channel, you’ll find full coverage of Resident Evil 9, including gameplay analysis, story breakdowns, trailer reactions, and all the latest news from Gamescom 2025 and beyond. If you’re a true Resident Evil fan, make sure to subscribe so you don’t miss a single update about Resident Evil Requiem.

snippet.title: Sekiro: No Defeat | Official Trailer | Crunchyroll
snippet.description:
Sekiro: No Defeat is coming exclusively to Crunchyroll!

The time is Sengoku.

Japan is fractured into many independent nations entangled in ceaseless war. At the center lies Ashina, a land of sacred earth and ancient mystery. Two decades after Sword Saint Isshin Ashina reclaimed the region in a brutal coup, a new threat emerges from within: The Interior Ministry. Desperate to protect his homeland, Isshin’s grandson Genichiro turns to forbidden powers. The only hope lies in a kidnapped boy — the Divine Heir — and his silent protector: a loyal shinobi known only as Sekiro.

This is the story of a lord and his retainer — and their quest to restore balance to a nation on the edge.

Crunchyroll brings you the latest clips, openings, full episodes, and more from your favorite anime!

snippet.title: Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War IV Official Announce Trailer | Gamescom Opening Night 2025
snippet.description:
At last, back to war! Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War IV officially revealed during Gamescom Opening Night Live 2025!

Battle for planet Kronus as Warhammer 40,000's ultimate real time strategy game returns, featuring the largest campaign ever with four distinct factions battling it out in epic, brutal large-scale conflicts. 

Dawn of War IV returns to the legendary RTS series’ roots with satisfying gameplay and a brutal, expanded Sync Kill system. Take command of four Warhammer 40,000 factions, including, for the first time in the Dawn of War series, the Adeptus Mechanicus! Fight through 70+ campaign missions solo or with a friend in a story crafted by legendary Black Library author John French. Immerse yourself in endlessly replayable modes including Last Stand and Skirmish, or take the fight to the world with intense multiplayer combat.

Read more on Warhammer Community: https://www.warhammer-community.com/en-gb/articles/l8pdgqps/warhammer-40000-dawn-of-war-iv/

[Interludio]
Come on
You know who's the best [?]
The King
Copy?

[Verso 2]
Para ti, "Hasta siempre te amaré" fue un refrán

Please, please

Take me with you tomorrow
Take me and I won't bother

Tomorrow, tomorrow

Tomorrow, tomorrow

¿Y si digo que es una de las mejores canciones jamás creadas? Gracias Joan Sebastian por tan grande letra y grande Chente por esta interpretación 🧡🍐

"Un Millón de Primaveras" escrita por Joan Sebastian y popularizada por Vicente Fernández, habla sobre el dolor de la pérdida de un ser querido, específicamente un hijo, y el proceso de duelo del padre, quien habla con su hijo fallecido, prometiéndole que, aunque le costará un millón de primaveras olvidarlo, eventualmente lo hará.

→ Sigue escuchando "Un Millón de Primaveras":
https://open.spotify.com/track/6j5LtifAnuTjTYvml61yFZ?si=017f5f49a6654c2e

→ Lyrics:
[Letra de "Millón de Primaveras"]

[Verso 1]
Te molesta si te hablo de mi amor
Y me pides, por favor, olvide el tema
Y que cambie la letra de mis canciones
Y tu nombre quite ya de aquel poema
Te molesta; aguanta, por favor
Te lo juro, estoy a punto de olvidarte

[Coro]
Solo falta un millón de primaveras
Unos cuantos siglos solo he de adorarte
Solo falta un millón de primaveras
Después de eso ya no vuelvo a molestarte
Oh no, no volveré a cantarte
Si te molesta, si te molesta

[Verso 2]
Te molesta el perro que ladró
De alegría, anunciando tu llegada
Y me dices que ese perro está loco
Que le ladra a la persona equivocada
Yo te digo: "Por favor, aguanta un poco"
"Ten paciencia, no le des otra pedrada"
Oh no, no volverá a ladrarte
Si te molesta, si te molesta

[Coro]
Solo falta un millón de primaveras
Unos cuantos siglos solo he de adorarte
Solo falta un millón de primaveras
Después de eso ya no vuelvo a molestarte
Oh no, no volveré a cantarte
Si te molesta, si te molesta

[Outro]
Si te molesta, si te molesta

[Intro]

Vos que andás diciendo que se debe hacer

Pero qué poco nos enseñan de amor

Que no la tiene
Nunca piensa
Nunca piensa (¡Va!)

¡Mambo!

[Coro: Flavio Cianciarulo, (Los Fabulosos Cadillacs & Mick Jones)]
(¡Mal bicho!)
Todos te dicen que sos
(¡Mal bicho!)
Así es como te ves
(¡Mal bicho!)

(¡Mal bicho!)
Que-se-ge, se-ge, se, se

Todos te dicen que sos
(¡Mal bicho!)
Así es como te ves
(¡Mal bicho!)
Sen-ge, se-ge, se, se
(¡Mal bicho!)
Que-re-que, te-que, ten, ten

[Puente 3: Vicentico, (Flavio Cianciarulo)]
Vos que vas lastimando a quién se ve distinto
Imponiendo posturas
Siempre con mano dura
(¡Si!)
(¡Va!)
(¡Si!)

[Verso 3: Mick Jones]
Mal bicho, your destiny is bad
Mal bicho, which marks your path
Mal bicho, the song that is brave
Mal bicho, is a song for always
Mal bicho, so you make the wars
Mal bicho, write your false laws
Mal bicho, you love it man
Mal bicho, man, you don't give a damn

[Pre-Coro: Flavio Cianciarulo]
¡Mambo!

[Coro: Flavio Cianciarulo, (Los Fabulosos Cadillacs & Mick Jones)]
(¡Mal bicho!)
Todos te dicen que sos
(¡Mal bicho!)
Así es como te ves
(¡Mal bicho!)
Sen-ge, se-ge, se, se
(¡Mal bicho!)
Que-se-ge, se-ge, se, se
(¡Mal bicho!)
Todos te dicen que sos
(¡Mal bicho!)
Así es como te ves
(¡Mal bicho!)
Sen-ge, se-ge, sen, sen
(¡Mal bicho!)
Que-re-que, te-que, ten, ten

[Puente 4: Vicentico & Mick Jones]
Vos tenés pal'abrigo
Otros mueren de frío
Sos el que anda matando
El que va torturando

[Coro: Flavio Cianciarulo, (Los Fabulosos Cadillacs & Mick Jones)]
(¡Mal bicho!)
Todos te dicen que sos
(¡Mal bicho!)
Así es como te ves
(¡Mal bicho!)
Sen-ge, se-ge, se, se
(¡Mal bicho!)
Que-re-que, te-que, ten, ten

[Interludio: Flavio Cianciarulo]
¡Alelú, alelú!
(¡Sí!)

[Outro: Vicentico]
Yo no voy
A la guerra
A la violencia
A la injusticia
Y a tu codicia
Digo ¡no!
Digo ¡no!
Digo ¡no!, digo ¡no!, digo ¡no!
Digo ¡no!
Digo ¡no!
Digo ¡no!, digo ¡no!, digo ¡no!
Paz en el mundo
Que no hay paz en el mundo
